## Cumulative Analysis

### Definition
Cumulative Analysis calculates the running total of a metric over time, providing an aggregated view that accumulates values as time progresses.

---

### Purpose
- Track the overall progress of key metrics across periods  
- Understand total contribution over time rather than isolated snapshots  
- Identify trends in growth, accumulation, or depletion of measures  

---

### Why It’s Used
- Useful for sales, revenue, or production tracking over a year, quarter, or month  
- Helps stakeholders monitor cumulative performance against goals or targets  
- Supports forecasting and planning by visualizing ongoing progress  

---

### Formula

**Examples:**
- Running Total of Sales by Year  
- Moving Average of Sales by Month  

-- Advanced Data analysis
-- Cumulative Analysis
-- Calculate the total sales per month and the running total of salves over time.

SELECT
	order_date,
	total_sales,

--  *** WINDOWS FUNCTION ***

-- Running Totals
	SUM(total_sales) OVER(ORDER BY order_date) AS Running_Total_Sales, -- Keeps Cumulating year-by-year
	SUM(total_sales) OVER(PARTITION BY order_date ORDER BY order_date) AS NewRunning_Total_Sales, -- Cumulation resets from each New Year

-- Moving Average
	AVG(Avg_Price) OVER(ORDER BY order_date) AS Moving_agv_price,
	AVG(Avg_Price) OVER(PARTITION BY order_date ORDER BY order_date) AS NewMoving_agv_price

FROM
--Sales Table Subquery
(
SELECT
	DATETRUNC(MONTH, order_date) AS Order_date,
	SUM(sales_amount) AS Total_Sales,
	AVG(price) AS Avg_Price
FROM
	Gold.fact_sales

WHERE order_date IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY DATETRUNC(month, order_date)
) t

-- Cumulate By Year (Allot more Clean then previous select query

SELECT
	order_date,
	total_sales,

-- WINDOWS FUNCTION
	SUM(total_sales) OVER(ORDER BY order_date) AS Running_Total_Sales,  -- Keeps Cumulating year-by-year
	AVG(Avg_Price) OVER(ORDER BY order_date) AS Moving_agv_price -- Keeps Cumulating year-by-year
FROM
--Sales Table Subquery
(
SELECT
	DATETRUNC(YEAR, order_date) AS Order_date,
	SUM(sales_amount) AS Total_Sales,
	AVG(price) AS Avg_Price
FROM
	Gold.fact_sales

WHERE order_date IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY DATETRUNC(YEAR, order_date)
) t
